	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jun 3rd 2:35 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi all fellow monkeys.&nbsp;&nbsp;I just reached level 17. A very important level in a monks life and put 20 skill points into Feign death giving me a skill of (37).  Im currently hunting crocs in Oasis and they dont seem to fall for the fake death.  What im wondering is if you wise monks can tell me at what skill does feign start to be reliabel?  I've read many posts here and hear alot about great feign pulling but can i ever really trust the skill?  Thanks for all your help this is my first post and this site has given me much insite on monkly ways.  Be safe and hit um fast and hit um hard!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99156741450624></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99156741450624><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99156741450624>RE: Feign Death</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99156741450624#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>171 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jun 3rd 7:23 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you see the message "Osano has fallen to the ground", your FD failed (replace Osano with whatever your char. name is).&nbsp;&nbsp;The MOB doesn't believe you, and will keep attacking.  You will see this message a LOT at 37 skill.<br><br>If you get NO message at all, your FD worked (with some notable exceptions, including a couple bugs).  If you're soloing however, and not fighting a casting MOB, your FD should have worked if you get no message.<br><br>FD starts becoming more reliable starting around skill level 50, and is quite reliable once it reaches 100.  You will still fail even with double mastery, but much much more rarely (of course, with what you're likely to be pulling at that point, fails can be deadly).<br><br>My recomendation is to feign fish (just cast and FD repeatedly .. get some food while you practice) until at least skill level 50.  Is this boring? Yes.  Is it worth the time invested? YES.<br><br>I turned 17 in Oasis too and would kill a caiman or whatever and then run out to one of the spires in the water and feign fish until back to full health.  You heal at standing instead of sitting rate, but if you've kept up with practicing your mend skill, your mend should be more reliable by now, so that helps.<br><br>Until you get FD close to 100, try to make an EARLY judgment about how the battle is going against the MOB and FD if you're down to half health and it looks like the MOB might win.  This gives you room to fail once or twice.  You can start feigning later and later in battles as you increase in skill, thus giving you more chances to 'catch up' against a MOB who might have gotten in a few lucky shots early.<br><br>A few important notes:<br><br>*Auto-attack must be OFF, or your attempt to FD will fail.  A lot of monks make a hotkey macro (through the social keys) to both turn off auto-attack and FD.<br><br>* If you're fighting/pulling a casting MOB and you FD AFTER the MOB starts to cast, the spell will break FD.  As you learn how to use FD, you will learn to time your feigns against casters so you FD immediately after being hit by a spell.<br><br>* If you're in a group, FD will sometimes fail even though you get no message.  This is considered a bug by monks and a 'feature' by Verant (surprise, surprise).  This only seems to happen if the MOB is aggro on the group and not just you as the puller, but it can make 'bouncing' aggro through FD difficult.<br><br>* Spells by group members on you while FD can also break feign.  If you're damage shilded, the shield will break feign.  Remind that helpful cleric in your group NOT to heal you while you're feign pulling even if you're getting whacked a bit.  Get your heal after you're back to the group.  Tell that Druid NOT to damage shield you if you're feign pulling.<br><br>* Once you start to use FD to split MOBs to pull to groups, remember to FD far enough away from your group so that your group is still outside the aggro radius of the MOBs while you 'sort' them.  Sorting is where you wait for an appropriate number to wander away before you pop (stand back up) and bring the one(s) you want back to the group.  Personally, I don't recommend doing this until at least 75 skill, but if you have a patient group of friends with at least one good healer for fails, it can be done at 50.<br><br>* MOB behavior changes DRASTICALLY if the MOB is level 35+ (much harder to mem-wipe with FD, among other things), but you won't have to worry about that for a while.<br><br>Welcome to the true pleasure of being a monk -- keep your FD skill up and you will likely have a blast (except when practicing -- YAWN).<br><br>(Edited to include having to turn auto-attack off, which I somehow managed to forget to note the first time around -- thanks to follow-up poster for catching this).<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
